## When to Use MMR

**1. In a RAG pipeline** — to avoid feeding the LLM redundant documents
- e.g. LangChain topics: FAISS, Agents, Memory, Prompt Chain, Hybrid Retrieval
- → Result is richer, more useful context for the LLM

**2. Chatbots** — FAQ, Search App, Document Browser

**3. When the retriever already returns many results** + you need diversity

**4. MMR + Hybrid Retrieval** → Dense + Sparse (best of all worlds)

---

## When NOT to Use MMR

| Scenario | Why You Might Skip MMR |
|---|---|
| Extremely short context window | You may just want top-1 most relevant |
| You need **precision only** | Not focused on coverage |
| Documents are already diverse | No need to enforce diversity |
| You're already reranking with LLM | Redundancy handled by post-filtering |

---

**Quick Rule of Thumb:**
- Use MMR when **breadth/coverage** matters
- Skip MMR when **precision** matters or redundancy is already handled downstream (e.g. by LLM reranking like in the previous notebook)
